<div id="best-book-lists/liverpool-fc-books">
    <div id="breadcrumb" class="breadcrumb"><div class="manual"><ul><li><span class="ui-sortable-handle"><a href="/">Home</a></span></li><li><span class="ui-sortable-handle"><a href="/best-book-lists">Best Book Lists</a></span></li><li><span><a href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/best-book-lists/liverpool-fc-books">Liverpool FC books</a></span></li></ul></div></div>

    <div class="container-md">
   <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12">
   
<div class="headers  twenty no">
  <h1 style="font-size: 32px;">
  
  
      
        The 11 best Liverpool FC books
        
        
    
    
    </h1>
</div>

<div class="headers  fourty yes">
  
  
  <h3 style="font-size: 20px;">
      
        There are Liverpool FC books for all appetites and ages, from histories and official publications to autobiographies and annuals. Here’s a line-up of 11 unbeatable titles
        
        
    </h3>
    
    
</div>

<div class="basicTextBlock  twenty"><p>What do you buy the fan of the team who have won everything? Fortunately, there are Liverpool FC books on all aspects of the most successful club in English football history, from a Steven Gerrard autobiography as uncompromising as the player himself to a Jurgen Klopp book &ndash;<i> I Feel Fine </i>&ndash; that sings of the Kop&rsquo;s love for their German manager.&nbsp;</p>

<p>No club has made more headlines than Liverpool and this selection of titles kicks off with a <strong><a href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Liverpool-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/27331426"><i>Telegraph Custom Gift Book</i></a></strong> that reproduces back-page stories from the paper charting more than 120 years of the club&rsquo;s highs and lows.<i> Hillsborough &ndash; The Truth</i> is the definitive account of that tragedy and the 30-year fight for justice by survivors and supporters.</p>

<p>Also included in this round-up of Liverpool Football Club gifts for Reds who love to read is an autobiography of &#39;the Voice of Anfield&rsquo; George Sephton, the stadium announcer since 1971, and <i>Red Men Reborn</i>, a social history of the club. Add in annuals and colouring books for kids and a 1,000 question quiz book and you can <i>Call Yourself a Reds Fan </i>too<i>.</i></p>
</div>

</div>
   </div>
</div>
<div class="container-md">
   <div class="row">
      <div class="col-12 listicle-header__wrapper twenty yes">
   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--center">
      
      Liverpool Football Club gift books
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock  fourty"><p>There are Liverpool FC books for all generations of those who follow the most successful English football club in history. And the city is a place where football allegiances run in the family like no other in England. So here&rsquo;s something for everyone from eight to 80.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p></div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//books.telegraph.co.uk/RichContent/Products/9781472632227/ProductImage/074769ae-c280-4596-9447-f877a6625b4c_medium.jpg" alt="Liverpool Football Headlines - The Telegraph Custom Gift Book"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Liverpool-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/27331426">Liverpool Football Headlines - The Telegraph Custom Gift Book</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">The ultimate Liverpool FC book, this personalised volume charts the history of England’s most successful club from 1901 – the year of their first league title – through reproduced articles, reports and images from The Telegraph archive. It captures the highs of 18 more championships, six European Cup wins and countless magical nights at Anfield, plus the lows of Heysel and Hillsborough and the three-decade fight for justice. Of all Liverpool FC books, this one illustrates how the club has produced players and personalities few rivals can match, from Bill Shankly to Jurgen Klopp via Bob Paisley and Kenny Dalglish.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Liverpool-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/27331426">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97818395/9781839501043.jpg" alt="Call Yourself a Reds Fan? : The Ultimate Liverpool Quiz Book"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Mart-Matthews/Call-Yourself-a-Reds-Fan--The-Ultimate-Liverpool-Quiz-Book/27083947">Call Yourself a Reds Fan? : The Ultimate Liverpool Quiz Book</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">How well do you know the history of Liverpool FC? This book by Mart Matthews will give you an answer to that and 1,000 more questions the author has compiled in 100 eclectic categories. Be warned, even the most knowledgeable Kopites may be left scratching their heads over which star players share their names with famous racehorses. And while most Reds can think of a link between the club and The Beatles, where do Napoleon, Moby-Dick, The Big Bang Theory and Bob Dylan fit into the picture? The answers are here.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Mart-Matthews/Call-Yourself-a-Reds-Fan--The-Ultimate-Liverpool-Quiz-Book/27083947">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819145/9781914536274.jpg" alt="Liverpool Classic Kits"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Rob-Mason/Liverpool-Classic-Kits/26788241">Liverpool Classic Kits</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Liverpool’s legendary manager Bill Shankly transformed the club in the 1960s. But he didn’t just make them a footballing force at home and in Europe – he also changed their home strip to the all-red with which they have been synonymous ever since. “The players looked like giants and we played like giants,” the Scot said after it was first worn against Anderlecht in 1964. Rob Mason’s colourful volume collates Liverpool’s classic kits of all colours – and did you know they began life in 1892 in the blue of the city’s other club?</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Rob-Mason/Liverpool-Classic-Kits/26788241">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819158/9781915879233.jpg" alt="The Official Liverpool FC Annual"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/The-Official-Liverpool-FC-Annual/28652817">The Official Liverpool FC Annual</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Celebrate your passion for the Reds with the official 2024 Liverpool Annual. Jam-packed with features and photographs that document the 2022-23 season, plus facts, stats and features that make it essential reading for every true Liverpool fan. Discover more about all aspects of life at the club and get the inside track from the stars at the forefront of the quest for success under Jurgen Klopp, including some of the new arrivals. On and off the pitch, a new era is dawning at Anfield so read all about it in this official publication.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/The-Official-Liverpool-FC-Annual/28652817">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819141/9781914197673.jpg" alt="This is Anfield : The Illustrated History of Liverpool Football Club's Matchday Programme"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Liverpool-FC/This-is-Anfield--The-Illustrated-History-of-Liverpool-Foo/28179522">This is Anfield : The Illustrated History of Liverpool Football Club's Matchday Programme</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Subtitled The Illustrated History of Liverpool’s Football Club’s Matchday Programme, this fascinating volume offers an alternative take on the history of the Reds. It charts how the official programme has evolved from 1892 to the present day, becoming the voice of the club and an important part of the matchday experience for supporters. Compiled by Reds fan and programme collector Andy Marsden, it includes several unseen images from his comprehensive archive and is an essential and evocative guide to the club’s glorious past.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Liverpool-FC/This-is-Anfield--The-Illustrated-History-of-Liverpool-Foo/28179522">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="basicBanner fourty ">
   <a href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Bob-Mortimer/The-Satsuma-Complex/27136859"><img src="/Content/StoreFront/assets/images/BookOTM.png.png" alt="" class="" /></a>
</div><div class="col-12 listicle-header__wrapper twenty yes">
   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--center">
      
      Liverpool FC player books and autobiographies
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock padding fourty"><p style="line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;">Plenty of great names have been associated with Liverpool and this selection features two of the most prominent, Steven Gerrard and Jurgen Klopp, as well as two from behind the scenes, assistant coach Pep Linders and long-time stadium announcer George Sephton.</p>
</div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97814059/9781405924412.jpg" alt="My Story"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Steven-Gerrard/My-Story/18585656">My Story</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">Steven Gerrard’s autobiography is one of a kind. The former Liverpool and England captain played 710 matches for the club from 1998 to 2015, becoming the first player to score in finals of the Champions League, FA Cup, Uefa Cup and League Cup while racking up 186 Liverpool goals. Gerrard’s book is as unflinching as he was on the pitch, and he discusses with candour highs – the ‘Miracle of Istanbul’ in the 2005 Champions League final – and lows such as missing out on the Premier League title in 2014, plus the great players he lined up with and against, the managers he played for and England’s “golden generation”.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Steven-Gerrard/My-Story/18585656">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819141/9781914197451.jpg" alt="Liverpool FC: I Feel Fine, The Klopp 100 : A Modern Liverpool Love Affair"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Liverpool-Football-Club/Liverpool-FC-I-Feel-Fine-The-Klopp-100--A-Modern-Liverpool-Love-Affair/27486256">Liverpool FC: I Feel Fine, The Klopp 100 : A Modern Liverpool Love Affair</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">A love story. Just as the Kop adapted The Beatles’ song I Feel Fine into a hymn of praise to the club’s charismatic manager Jurgen Klopp, so Chris McLoughlin and Roy Gilfoyle’s book in his honour is subtitled A Modern Liverpool Love Affair. It details 100 magical, memorable moments from the eight-year reign of the German. From the Hendo shuffle to goalkeeper Alisson scoring with a header, this is a Liverpool FC history book with a difference, celebrating the memories that matter as much to fans as the wins.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Liverpool-Football-Club/Liverpool-FC-I-Feel-Fine-The-Klopp-100--A-Modern-Liverpool-Love-Affair/27486256">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97818389/9781838952709.jpg" alt="The Voice of Anfield : My Fifty Years with Liverpool FC"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/George-author-Sephton/The-Voice-of-Anfield--My-Fifty-Years-with-Liverpool-FC/26872903">The Voice of Anfield : My Fifty Years with Liverpool FC</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">George Sephton has been the voice of Anfield since 1971, when he applied to become the stadium announcer. He and Kevin Keegan made their home debuts on the same day, but George has lasted almost 50 years longer at Liverpool than the legendary former captain. His book offers a fan’s-eye view of life at the club, and recalls his times with some of the great figures, such as Bill Shankly, John Barnes and Kenny Dalglish, the last of whom contributes the foreword and describes George as “part of the brickwork of the club”.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/George-author-Sephton/The-Voice-of-Anfield--My-Fifty-Years-with-Liverpool-FC/26872903">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819141/9781914197482.jpg" alt="Intensity : Inside Liverpool FC"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Pep-Lijnders/Intensity--Inside-Liverpool-FC/27143310">Intensity : Inside Liverpool FC</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">In his own engaging and inspiring style, assistant manager Pep Linders takes readers behind the scenes at Anfield during the 2021-22 season, from the club’s training centre and the team hotel to the pitch, the dugout and the dressing room. In forming a “one club” mentality, Jurgen Klopp, Lijnders and Co have also created countless modern memories for the LFC family, and this book chronicles their legacy, as well as offering a unique account of a season at Anfield from one of the game's most thoughtful students.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Pep-Lijnders/Intensity--Inside-Liverpool-FC/27143310">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 listicle-header__wrapper fourty yes">
   <h2 class="listicle-header__header listicle-header__header--">
      
      History of Liverpool FC
      
      
   </h2>
</div>
<div class="basicTextBlock  "><p>Thought-provoking takes on the people&rsquo;s game: the definitive account of the Hillsborough tragedy and an insight into the bitterest rivalry in English football.&nbsp;</p></div>
<div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97818015/9781801501507.jpg" alt="Red Men Reborn! : A Social History of Liverpool Football Club from John Houlding to Jurgen Klopp"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/John-Williams/Red-Men-Reborn--A-Social-History-of-Liverpool-Football-Cl/26823042">Red Men Reborn! : A Social History of Liverpool Football Club from John Houlding to Jurgen Klopp</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">John Williams examines Liverpool FC’s history and socio-cultural significance, brilliantly weaving his narrative around the great managers from Tom Watson, Bill Shankly and Bob Paisley to Kenny Dalglish, Rafa Benitez and Jurgen Klopp. The book shines a spotlight on the period after 2010, when the club faced an ownership crisis and possible extinction. It also studies Klopp, his broader influences and his key hiring and coaching practices, to explain the club’s incredible reversal of fortune and remarkable recent success.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/John-Williams/Red-Men-Reborn--A-Social-History-of-Liverpool-Football-Cl/26823042">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  <div class="col-12 articleList article--center article--underline">
      <div class="article__image-wrapper"><img src="//tmg.dmmserver.com/media/356/97819109/9781910948019.jpg" alt="Hillsborough - The Truth"></div>
      <div class="article__content">
          <div class="article__header">
              <h3><a  href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Professor-Phil-Scraton/Hillsborough---The-Truth/18152047">Hillsborough - The Truth</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="article__desc">The definitive account of the 1989 tragedy in which 96 Liverpool supporters who went to watch the FA Cup semi-final against Nottingham Forest at Hillsborough were unlawfully killed owing to grossly negligent failures by the emergency services. (The death toll has since risen to 97.) Professor Scraton was the primary author of the report published by the Hillsborough Independent Panel and this book details how, when it came to Hillsborough, the truth took 27 years of campaigning by bereaved families and survivors to establish. It stands as an important, harrowing account that exposes institutional complacency.</div>
          <div class="article__cta"><a  class="button btn" href="https://books.telegraph.co.uk/Product/Professor-Phil-Scraton/Hillsborough---The-Truth/18152047">Buy now</a></div>          
      </div>
  </div>
   
  
